EPISTLE VII.

On retirIng into the country, Horace had promised his patron that he would return in five days. But after spending the whole month of August, he writes this epistle to Maecenas, by way of apology for breaking his engagement. The natural and easy manner in which Horace excuses himself to his illustrious friend, shows that it is possible to enjoy the favor of the great without sacrificing one’s independence, or descending to servilit .
